            <text>3.3.1.4 Task: Coefficient of linear [NOT IN QUIZ]</text>
        </name>
        <questiontext format="html">
            <text><![CDATA[
<p class="HELM_exercise">
    Exercise
</p>
<p>
    If \({@aa@} x^2 + {@d1@} x + {@d2@} = (x + {@dd@}) \times \hbox{ (a polynomial)}\), what must be the coefficient of \(x\) in this unknown polynomial?&#160;[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]
</p>
]]></text>
        </questiontext>
        <generalfeedback format="html">
            <text><![CDATA[
<p>
    We are given \({@aa@} x^2 + {@d1@} x + {@d2@} = (x + {@dd@}) \times \hbox{ (a polynomial)}\). We know that the polynomial multiplied by a linear function, \(x + {@dd@}\), must give a quadratic. Therefore the polynomial must also be a linear function,
                i.e. the polynomial is of the form \(ax + b\). Therefore
</p>
<p>
    \[(x + {@dd@})(ax + b) = ax^2 + (a\cdot{@dd@} + b)x + b \cdot {@dd@}\].
</p>
<p>
    Comparing coefficients of the \(x^2\) terms we see that \(a={@aa@}\).
</p>
]]></text>
        </generalfeedback>
